title: Who left Strictly Come Dancing last night in the third elimination?
text:
Another one bites the dust… (Picture: PA)

From Kelvin Fletcher’s hips to the constant churning of the ‘Strictly curse’ rumour mill, Strictly Come Dancing sure is delivering this year.

But Strictly giveth, and Strictly taketh away, as every week, we must say goodbye to a celebrity as they are eliminated from the show.

For anyone who missed last night’s results episode, here’s who ended up leaving the lineup week…

Who left Strictly Come Dancing last night?

Despite not being at the very bottom of the leaderboard, Dev Griffin has been the third celeb contestant to be sent home from Strictly.

Dev and partner Dianne Buswell were awarded 26 points in total from the judges, however, after the public vote, they one of the two lowest-scoring pairs of the week along with Viscountess Emma Weymouth and Aljaž Škorjanec, who scored 28 points.

After both couples then went head-to-head in a dance-off, the duo that the judges chose to save was Emma and Aljaž.

The Strictly Come Dancing leaderboard results for episode four Alex Scott and Neil Jones – 23 Will Bayley and Janette Manrara – 24 Chris Ramsay and Karen Hauer – 26 Dev Griffin and Dianne Buswell – 27 David James and Nadiya Bychkova – 28 Viscountess Emma Weymouth and Aljaž Škorjanec – 28 Catherine Tyldesley and Johannes Radebe – 30 Michelle Visage and Giovanni Pernice – 31 Mike Bushell and Katya Jones – 32 Saffron Barker and AJ Pritchard – 33 Emma Barton and Anton Du Beke – 35 Kelvin Fletcher and Oti Mabuse – 36 Karim Zeroual and Amy Dowden – 38

Afterwards, Dev told co-host Tess Daly: ‘I’m not going to lie I am absolutely gutted, but learning how to dance, hanging out with Dianne and the other pros and celebs… I’ve absolutely loved it.’

Dianne’s parting words on her radio DJ partner were: ‘Dev has been absolutely amazing. His work ethic is insane.’

‘I see him everywhere practising and I couldn’t have asked for a better partner. Thank you so much for all your time and your effort. This boy has so much talent, I’m really sad he won’t be able to show you guys any more of it.’

Strictly Come Dancing continues on Saturday on BBC One.
